alluxio

Class Configuration

  • java.lang.Object
    • alluxio.Configuration

  • @NotThreadSafe
public final class Configuration
extends Object

    All the runtime configuration properties of Alluxio. This class works like a dictionary and serves each Alluxio configuration property as a key-value pair.

    Alluxio configuration properties are loaded into this class in the following order with decreasing priority:

    1. Java system properties;
    2. Environment variables via alluxio-env.sh or from OS settings;
    3. Site specific properties via alluxio-site.properties file;
    4. Default properties via alluxio-default.properties file.

    The default properties are defined in a property file alluxio-default.properties distributed with Alluxio jar. Alluxio users can override values of these default properties by creating alluxio-site.properties and putting it under java CLASSPATH when running Alluxio (e.g., ${ALLUXIO_HOME}/conf/)
